15/08/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The government announced on Tuesday (August 14th) it is sending surplus weapons and ammunition to Afghanistan as a contribution to the fight against terrorism.
The country plans to donate about 150 automatic rifles, 100 machine guns and 250,000 bullets to Afghan troops battling Taliban militants.
Montenegro received the surplus weapons after its split with Serbia last year.
(Vijesti - 15/08/07;
HINA, AP - 14/08/07)
